        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 7:41PM CDT until August 24 at 8:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Wheeler County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 830 PM CDT.

* At 740 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles northwest
of Allison, or 19 miles southeast of Canadian, moving south at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Allison.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
